# ============================================================================
# .dockerignore - Docker Build Context Exclusions
# ============================================================================
#
# Educational Note: This file tells Docker which files to IGNORE when building
# Similar to .gitignore for Git, but for Docker builds
#
# Why use .dockerignore?
# - Faster builds (less data to send to Docker daemon)
# - Smaller images (excluded files won't be copied)
# - Better security (don't copy secrets accidentally)
# - Cleaner builds (no temporary or generated files)
#
# Think of it as: "Don't load this cargo onto the ship"
#
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Git and Version Control
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github

# Educational Note: We don't need Git history inside the container
# The .git folder can be very large and serves no purpose in production

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python Cache and Compiled Files
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python

# Educational Note: Python creates these when running
# They're regenerated in the container, so no need to copy them

# Build artifacts
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Virtual Environments
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
env/
venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/

# Educational Note: Virtual environments are for local development
# The container creates its own isolated environment

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IDE and Editor Files
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# Educational Note: Editor configurations are personal preferences
# They don't belong in production containers

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Documentation and Development Files
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
README.md
PHASE4_TESTING.md
docs/TUTORIAL_GUIDE.md
docs/EXAMPLE_COMMANDS.md
*.md
!requirements.md

# Educational Note: Documentation is for humans reading the code
# The running app doesn't need it (but README could be included if desired)
# The ! prefix means "don't ignore this file" (exception to *.md)

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Testing
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
tests/
test_*.py
*_test.py
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.tox/

# Educational Note: Tests are for development and CI/CD
# Production containers don't need test files

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker Files
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
.docker/

# Educational Note: These files are for building the image
# The running container doesn't need them
# (The Dockerfile is the blueprint - the ship doesn't carry its own blueprint!)

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs and Temporary Files
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
logs/
*.tmp
tmp/
temp/

# Educational Note: Logs and temp files from local development
# Containers create their own logs at runtime

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Database Files (Optional - depends on your setup)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment if you want to exclude local database and regenerate in container
# *.sqlite
# *.db
# data/tutorials.sqlite

# Educational Note: For this app, we DO copy the database
# because it contains tutorial content
# But in many apps, you'd exclude databases and use external storage

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment and Secrets
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
secrets/
credentials/

# Educational Note: CRITICAL - never copy secrets into images!
# Secrets should be:
# - Passed as environment variables at runtime
# - Mounted from secure secret stores
# - Never baked into images

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CI/CD
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.circleci/
.travis.yml
.gitlab-ci.yml
Jenkinsfile
.github/

# Educational Note: CI/CD configs are for automation pipelines
# They're not needed in the runtime container

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Node.js (if using any frontend build tools)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log
package-lock.json
yarn.lock

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS Generated Files
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.DS_Store
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

# Educational Note: OS-specific files that serve no purpose in Linux containers

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Large Media Files (if not needed in app)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# *.mp4
# *.avi
# *.mov
# *.zip
# *.tar.gz

# Educational Note: Large files increase image size significantly
# Only include media that's actually needed by the app

# ============================================================================
# Checking What Gets Copied
# ============================================================================
#
# To see what files would be included in your Docker build:
# docker build --no-cache -t test . 2>&1 | grep "Step"
#
# Or use a tool like dive to inspect layers:
# dive harbor-docker-learning
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# Best Practices Summary
# ============================================================================
#
# âœ… Exclude version control files (.git)
# âœ… Exclude virtual environments (env/, venv/)
# âœ… Exclude IDE configs (.vscode/, .idea/)
# âœ… Exclude build artifacts (__pycache__, *.pyc)
# âœ… Exclude documentation (*.md) unless needed
# âœ… Exclude tests (tests/, *_test.py)
# âœ… ALWAYS exclude secrets (.env, *.key)
# âœ… Exclude CI/CD configs (.github/, .gitlab-ci.yml)
# âœ… Exclude OS files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db)
# âœ… Exclude Docker files (Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml)
#
# Result: Faster builds, smaller images, better security!
#
# ============================================================================

